==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[coeliacus]], from Greek [[κοιλιακος]], from [[κοιλια]] ‘belly’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈsi:lɪæk/}}

===Adjective===
'''coeliac'''
# {{anatomy}} Relating to the [[abdomen]], or to the cavity of the abdomen.
# pertaining to [[coeliac disease]]

===Noun===
'''coeliac'''
# someone who has [[coeliac disease]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[celiac]]

